The paper proposes a framework for spam detection on Twitter using machine learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for tweet analysis, which suggests it could also belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also deals with security and privacy issues related to spam detection, which could place it in the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning algorithms for classification and detection also suggests it could belong to the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
